# Baqaya Rules

## Design Source

All designs are stored in:

design-reference/screens/<screen-name>/

Each contains:
- design.png
- layout.html

Use them as reference only.

---

## Critical Rule

Never convert HTML directly into React Native.

---

## Screen Implementation Workflow

1. Identify screen folder
2. Review design.png
3. Understand layout via HTML
4. Map to route
5. Build UI in React Native
6. Extract reusable components

---

## Folder Responsibilities

- app/ → routes/screens
- src/components/ → shared UI
- src/features/ → feature modules
- src/theme/ → design system
- src/utils/ → helpers
- src/services/ → API

---

## UI Rules

- Follow spacing and hierarchy from design
- Use consistent colors and typography
- Build mobile-first layouts
- Keep touch targets large

---

## Reusability

Always extract:
- Cards
- Buttons
- Inputs
- Tabs
- Banners
- Empty states

---

## Navigation

- Use Expo Router
- Separate auth and main app
- Keep routes simple

---

## Do NOT

- Do not copy HTML
- Do not mix design files into code
- Do not create large components
- Do not ignore design structure

---

## Output Expectation

- Clean code
- Modular components
- Design-aligned UI
- Proper folder usage